; Regression test for issue #1154: Pivot has confusing filtering properties (BZ#1154)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1154
;
; When --pivot is used, account filters are applied to ORIGINAL account names,
; not to the pivoted account names. This leads to confusing behavior:
;
; 1. Filtering by a pivoted account name (e.g., "Project:Alpha") returns empty
;    even though the pivoted output contains "Project:Alpha:*" accounts.
;
; 2. Transactions without the pivot tag appear mixed in with pivoted entries,
;    which is confusing when the user expects the pivot to organize all entries.

2024/01/01 Payee A
    ; Project: Alpha
    Expenses:Food    $10.00
    Assets:Cash

2024/01/02 Payee B
    ; Project: Beta
    Expenses:Other   $20.00
    Assets:Cash

2024/01/03 Payee C
    Expenses:Travel  $30.00
    Assets:Cash

; The full pivoted balance shows all transactions: tagged ones under Project:Alpha
; and Project:Beta, and the untagged one at the top level.
test bal --pivot Project
             $-30.00  Assets:Cash
              $30.00  Expenses:Travel
                   0  Project
                   0    Alpha
             $-10.00      Assets:Cash
              $10.00      Expenses:Food
                   0    Beta
             $-20.00      Assets:Cash
              $20.00      Expenses:Other
--------------------
                   0
end test

; Confusing behavior: filtering by "Project:Alpha" (the pivoted account prefix)
; returns empty, because the filter is applied to ORIGINAL account names
; (Expenses:Food, Assets:Cash) which don't match "Project:Alpha".
; Users would expect this to show only the Alpha project entries.
test bal --pivot Project Project:Alpha
end test

; Also confusing: filtering by "Expenses" works, but includes the untagged
; Expenses:Travel entry mixed with the pivoted Project:Alpha and Project:Beta
; entries, so the output structure is inconsistent.
test bal --pivot Project Expenses
              $30.00  Expenses:Travel
              $30.00  Project
              $10.00    Alpha:Expenses:Food
              $20.00    Beta:Expenses:Other
--------------------
              $60.00
end test
